verbose_text: This, along with the absence of the degranulation response of NK cells against healthy donor PBMCs, showed that the use of DNAM-1 + GM NK-92 cells could be restricted / directed only to targets that had elevated CD112 and/or CD155 expression (XREF_FIG, XREF_FIG), which is observed in tumors from various origins, including osteosarcomas.
